Class ParkingSpot

  • java.lang.Object
    • ParkingSpot

  • public class ParkingSpot
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a parking spot in a city. To create a new parking spot, you will use the Constructor. To print the details of the spot, you just need to print the object. 
    
 ParkingSpot spot = new ParkingSpot("Beacon St.", 1, 85);
 System.out.println(spot);
    Author:
    amit (original code), mvail (removed max duration variable and associated methods, conversion from double to int coordinates)
